Acuired Message

Diving into your subconscious was probably not the best idea. What even was that thing? It seemed inert until you got close. Oh well. That is in the past now. Important part is you made out alive... mostly unchanged... probably.

Template

Description: Your eyes protrude a bit. Your limbs have lengthened and are not quite proportional to how they used to be. A late life growth spurt? You are finding more hair in strange places. Well that is not quite right. Some areas seem smooth, almost slimy but that is not really too concerning. Unfortunate that your awkward teen years are returning. At least you are packing on muscle.

Weakness:

You flirt with the idea of sanity. Roll on the insanity table for time periods where the child is not borrowing power. This effect lasts until the end of the time period

Wild Magic: Spells you cast have a chance of turning out wrong. Roll a d100. On a 01 or 11 it goes wild.

Novice and Seasoned spells trigger rolls on weak effect table

Veteran spells trigger rolls on moderate effect table

Heroic spells trigger rolls on strong effect table

Legendary and Epic spells trigger rolls on unreal effect table

Transformation:

Triggers: When the child borrows powers (roll d100 on 00 the child takes over) or when you borrow the child (roll d100 on 01 the child takes over). If you are borrowing the child's power, you can choose to give in and transform without rolling.

The child takes over until you draw a face clubs, the time period ends, or you take 3 wounds in this form.

Your skin stretches and splits. Your eyes bulge and grow wide. Your limbs curl like tentacles pulverizing bone.

When the transformation ends you get set to your maximum number of wounds.

When the child is in control during non-combat interactions it will wander away from populated areas. Attempts to stop it will be seen as acts of aggression. It will expend all top tier spell slots remaining. Roll on related table (see Wild Magic). When the child is in control during combat, it considers all other entities hostile.

Powers:

Wild Magic: Spells cast on you have a chance of turning out wrong. Spellcaster rolls d100. On a 01 it goes wild.

Novice and Seasoned spells trigger rolls on weak effect table

Veteran spells trigger rolls on moderate effect table

Heroic spells trigger rolls on strong effect table

Legendary and Epic spells trigger rolls on unreal effect table

Transformation:

Triggers: When the child borrows powers (roll d100 on 00 the child takes over) or when you borrow the child (roll d100 on 01 the child takes over). If you are borrowing the child's power, you can choose to give in and transform without rolling.

The child takes over until you draw a face clubs, the time period ends, or you take 3 wounds in this form.

Your skin stretches and splits. Your eyes bulge and grow wide. Your limbs curl like tentacles pulverizing bone.

Your strength and vigor increase two steps (no limit), your parry increases by +2.

Your attacks do not follow any normal pattern. As if there is something just past your hand attacking for you. Fighting die increase one step

Eldritch Spawn Edges

Body Building Horror

Requirements: Acquired Race: Eldritch Spawn, Veteran

Your transformations have accustomed your body to greater strength than your peers. It truly is great that the scar tissue and bones set properly. Increase either your strength or vigor one step. Raise your strength AND vigor cap a step. This can be taken twice, however the other attribute must be chosen (taking twice will raise your caps two steps).

Mental Faculties, Moment of Clarity

Requirements: Acquired Race: Eldritch Spawn, Seasoned

Your mind doesn't feel quite right, no wait wrong actually normal, yeah that is it, it does not feel normal. Once per session you can ignore an insanity table roll.

Mental Faculties, Almost Lucid

Requirements: Acquired Race: Eldritch Spawn, Veteran, Moment of Clarity Mental Faculties

These abnormal days are becoming more common. You can ignore up to three rolls on the insanity table. This replaces Moment of Clarity.

Mental Faculties, Different Strokes

Requirements: Acquired Race: Eldritch Spawn, Novice

Some days you feel something coming and when it arrives it turns out to be completely different than expected. Once per session you may reroll one insanity table roll without a benny.

Mental Faculties, Rewire

Requirements: Acquired Race: Eldritch Spawn, Veteran, Different Strokes Mental Faculties

It's time to change your perspective. Three times per session you may reroll an insanity table roll without a benny. This replaces Different Strokes

Mental Faculties, Different Folks

Requirements: Acquired Race: Eldritch Spawn, Heroic, Moment of Clarity Mental Faculties, Different Strokes Mental Faculties

What is a gift if you can't share it with the people you love. You may use one negation (e.g. Moment of Clarity) AND one reroll (e.g. Different Strokes) to gift the insanity you just rolled to another person within conversation range (works across telepathy) for a time period. Choose whether or not you are still affected when you gift.

Mental Faculties, Best with Friends

Requirements: Acquired Race: Eldritch Spawn, Legendary, Different Folks Mental Faculties

They say sharing is caring and you care and can share. When you provide someone with an insanity you can mark them as friendly for a time period. If the child takes over during the time period they will consider the entity friendly (instead of hostile).

Wild Magic, Lost in Conversion

Requirements: Acquired Race: Eldritch Spawn, Heroic, Spirit d8

Magic sometimes just peters out when you are nearby. Almost like you are absorbing it. When a spell goes wild you may make a spirit check to lower what table it rolls on. A success lowers it one level (i.e. Novice=No roll, Seasoned=weak effect table, Legendary=strong effect table, Epic=unreal effect table). A raise lowers it two (i.e. Seasoned=No roll, Veteran=weak effect table, Legendary=moderate effect table, Epic=strong effect table). It can not be lowered more than two steps.

Wild Magic, What Conservation

Requirements: Acquired Race: Eldritch Spawn, Legendary, Spirit d10

Magic gushes out of you making things more eventful. When a spell goes wild you may make a spirit check to raise what table it rolls on. A success raise it one level (i.e. Novice=weak effect table, Seasoned=moderate effect table, Legendary=unreal effect table, Epic=unreal effect table+weak effect table). A raise increases the table two step (i.e. Novice=moderate effect table, Seasoned=strong effect table, Legendary=unreal effect table+weak effect table, Epic=unreal effect table+moderate effect table). It can not be increased more than two steps.

Wild Magic, Getting Interesting

Requirements: Acquired Race: Eldritch Spawn, Novice, Spirit d4

When spells go wrong, they go really wrong. When any spell double nat 1s within 4 Savage World inches, in addition to normal effects, have the caster roll on the equivalent table to that spell. This consumes a spell slot of that level. If the caster does not have one, they take a wound. The caster must roll a new spell casting roll for the tables result:

Double Nat 1: Triggers this again

Failure: Nothing more than consume the spell slot

Success: Consumes a spell slot AND triggers the tables effect

Single raise: Consume spell slot, Trigger Effect, OR Both

Double raise: No spell slot consumed. Optionally, Trigger Effect

Wild Magic, Party

Requirements: Acquired Race: Eldritch Spawn, Seasoned, Spirit d8, Getting Interesting Wild Magic

You worsen the results of spells. Instead of triggering rolls only on double nat 1s, you trigger Getting Interesting Wild Magic on any spell failure within 4 Savage World inches of you.

Wild Magic, VIP

Requirements: Acquired Race: Eldritch Spawn, Heroic, Spirit d8, Party Wild Magic

You can help your friends not blow themselves up. What would they do without you? Three times per session, when you trigger someone to roll on the wild magic tables, you can choose not to have them roll.

Transformation, Resilient

Requirements: Acquired Race: Eldritch Spawn, Novice

You are pretty hard to stop when your skin tears exposing the hard bone? Your transformation can take an additional wound before you are kicked out. This can be taken up to three times.

Transformation, Fireworks

Requirements: Acquired Race: Eldritch Spawn, Novice

Things start to happen when you lose it. When the child is in control during combat, make a spellcasting roll each round. This uses your highest spell slot to cast on its associated table (see Wild Magic). Raises do not consume a spell slot. This does not count as an action and therefore does not suffer multi-action penalties.

Transformation, Bigger on the Outside

Requirements: Acquired Race: Eldritch Spawn, Seasoned

While transformed you can reach deceptively far. You gain a Savage World inch of reach. This can be taken twice.

Resources

Insanity Table (d8)

1 -- You are effectively blind. Only able to see "active" magic. You gain a +4 to dispel "active" magical effects

2 -- You babble incoherently. No one can understand you. Gain a +2 to your spellcasting

3 -- Strange scents assault you constantly. Take a -2 to notice with another -2 to scent-based notices

4 -- You are constantly feeling stuff crawl all over you. Take a -2 to your spellcasting but your vigor and strength increase a die size

5 -- A sound track is blaring constantly. Surprisingly this helps you focus. Any task requiring you to focus alone gains a +2. Any task requiring you to work with other or split attention you have a -2 (these stack)

6 -- Your taste is way off. To keep anything down you must make a vigor roll

7 -- They say mind over matter. You are feeling that today. +2 to vigor rolls

8 -- Phantom creatures are constantly moving on your periphery. Your parry suffers a -4 but you gain a +4 gang up on others.

Weak effects (d6)

1 -- Close Targeted Damage -- Closest creature in small burst template takes 2d6 damage1 2

2 -- Far Targeted Damage -- Furthest creature in small burst template takes 2d6 damage1 2

3 -- Burst -- Damage1 2d10 Dir3:d8 Dist4:d6 Size:Small Burst Template

4 -- Cone -- Damage1 2d10 Dir3:d8 Cone Dir3:d8 Dist4:d6 Size:Small Cone

5 -- Teleport body (self): Dir3:d8 Dist:d6 KM

6 -- Potent (Upgrade) -- Roll on Moderate effects

Moderate effects (d8)

1 -- Multiple Weak -- Roll three Weak effects ignoring upgrade (6)

2 -- Burst -- Damage1 22d8 Dir3:d8 Dist4:d6 Size:Medium Burst Template

3 -- Cone -- Damage1 22d8 Dir3:d8 Cone Dir3:d8 Dist4:d6 Size:Medium Cone

4 -- Sleep -- Save:Spirit or Vigor Dir3:d8 Dist4:d6 Size:Small Burst Template

5 -- Targeted Damage -- Select 6 targets within Medium Burst Template. Roll 3d6; value of d6s are targets. Damage1 22d8. Can hit same person all three times.

6 -- Scramble Teleport -- Select 6 targets and assign numbers. Roll d6 to determine who is moved. Roll 3 times: Dir3:d8 Dist4:d6.

7 -- Double (Upgrade) -- Roll twice on Moderate effects. Ignore upgrades (7 and 8).

8 -- Potent (Upgrade) -- Roll on Strong effects table

Strong effects (d12)

1 -- Multiple Weak -- Roll five Weak effects ignoring upgrade (6)

2 -- Multiple Moderate -- Roll three Moderate effects ignoring upgrades (7 and 8)

3 -- Burst -- Damage1 22d10 Dir3:d8 Dist4:d12 Size:Large Burst Template

4 -- Cone -- Damage1 22d10 Dir3:d8 Cone Dir3:d8 Dist4:d12 Size:Large Cone

5 -- Targeted Damage -- Select 8 targets within Large Burst Template. Roll 7d8; value of d8s are targets. Damage1 22d12. Can hit same person all seven times.

6 -- Summon -- d6 minor Eldritch Horrors appear around corpse (GM controlled)

7 -- Mass Teleport -- Dir3:d8 Dist4:d12 Size:Medium Burst Template Effect: Teleport everything Dir3:d8 Dist4:4d12; If into object rejected for 2d12 damage otherwise normal Vigor save to avoid nausea AND Athletics or Agility to avoid falling

8 -- Warped Space -- Dir3:d8 Dist4:d12 Size:Large Burst Template Effect: Creatures caught inside see infinite copies of the space they are trapped in (including themselves). If they attempt to move out they end up on the other side (very hard to tell). Those who are caught on the edge when the space forms take 4d12+24 slicing, 4d12+24 bludgeoning, and 4d12+24 cold damage. Lasts d10 rounds.

9 -- Sleep -- Save:Spirit or Vigor Dir3:d8 Dist4:d6 Size:Large Burst Template; Lasts d6 rounds 10 -- Resurrection (Single) -- If you have gold to cover the resurrection on you, it is consumed along with 6 xp. You are alive again. This can only happen once per chain (death).

11 -- Double (Upgrade) -- Roll on Strong effect twice more. Ignore 12 (Infinite possible)

12 -- Potent (Upgrade) -- Roll on Unreal effects table

Unreal effects (d20)

1 -- Roll five Strong effects ignoring upgrades (11 and 12)

2 -- Burst -- 3 copies of Damage1 22d12+4 Dir3:d8 Dist4:d12 Size4:8 Radius

3 -- Cone -- 4 copies of Damage1 22d12+4 Dir3:d8 Cone Dir3:d8 Dist4:d12 Size4:8x5 Cone

4 -- Targeted Damage -- Select 20 targets within 25 SW inches. Roll 50d20; value of d20s are targets. Damage1 22d12+4. Can hit same person every time.

5 -- Time Freeze -- 3 copies of Dir3:d8 Dist4:2d12 Size:Large Burst Template Effect: Creatures caught in space are frozen in time for 2d10 rounds. Those caught on edge can take damage butcannot act.

6 -- Mass Scrambled Teleport -- 5 copies of Dir3:d8 Dist4:d12 Size:Large Burst Template Effect:Teleport everything 5 times Dir3:d8 Dist4:2d12

7 -- Reality Bubbles -- Roll Dir3:d8 Dist4:4d6 Size4:5 Radius Effect:Jungle appears in that space; Roll Dir3:d8 Dist4:4d6 Size4:5 Effect:Radius Ocean Depths appears in that space; Roll Dir3:d8 Dist4:4d6 Size4:5 Radius Effect:Hell scape appears in that space. All spaces function as Warped Space, not letting anything escape. Lasts 3d10 rounds

8 -- Horde -- summon 3d12+48 minor Eldritch Horrors (GM controlled)

9 -- Friends -- summon 1d12 minor Eldritch Horrors (player controlled); last 1d4-1 days

10 -- Eldritch Hallucinations -- Spirit save (opposed by Eldritch Incubator's), success = phobia until death, fail = perminate phobia, double nat 1 = death

11 -- Severed bonds -- Everyone within a 20 radius makes an opposed spirit roll. Failure = Attack closest creatures for 1d10 rounds.

12 -- Distorted Gravity -- Roll Dir3:d8 Dist4:4d6 Size4:5 Radius Effect: Zero-gravity in space; Roll Dir3:d8 Dist4:4d6 Size4:5 Radius Effect: Half-gravity in space; Roll Dir3:d8 Dist4:4d6 Size4:5 Radius Effect: Normal-gravity in space; Roll Dir3:d8 Dist4:4d6 Size4:5 Radius Effect: Double-gravity in space; Roll Dir3:d8 Dist4:4d6 Size4:5 Radius Effect: Octuple-gravity in space.

13 -- Gravity Well -- Dir3:d8 Dist4:d12 Size:Large Burst Template Effect: take 4d12+24 slicing, 4d12+24 bludgeoning, and 4d12+24 cold damage

14 -- Out of Time -- Roll Dir3:d8 Dist4:4d6 Size4:Large Burst Template Effect: Creatures in area disappear for 1d12 rounds. Only to reappear in the exact spot as if nothing happened.

15 -- Nap -- 5 copies Save:Lower of Spirit or Vigor Dir3:d8 Dist4:d12 Size:Large Burst Template; Lasts d6 minutes

16 -- Meteor shower -- At the start of each characters turn roll a d100. If not 10-90, then have them make an agility save at a -6. Failure = hit by meteor 2d12+4 piercing and 2d12+4 fire; Last 4d12 rounds

17 -- Body Swap -- Characters within 6 swap to bodies with another; Spirit negates; Lasts d12 rounds

18 -- Unraveling -- Creatures within 3 start to unravel and are unlikely to be able to move; Spirit negate; Lasts d12 rounds

19 -- Resurrection -- Ignore gold cost; Dir3:d8 Dist4:d8 Size4:6 Radius Effect: Resurrect everything as undead (up to your rank) or themselves. Eldritch Incubator loses 6 xp for each player resurrected. Players, not including the Eldritch Incubator, lose 6 xp too.

20 -- Potent (Upgrade) -- Roll on Unreal effects (ignore 20); Roll on Strong (Infinite possible)

Energy Table (d10)

1 -- No effect

2 -- Roll on Attribute Table, result decrease a die size (min d4-2)

3 -- Positive energy deals double damage, Negative heals double

4 -- Positive deals damage, Negative heals

5 -- Damage

6 -- Heal

7 -- Positive heals, Negative deals damage

8 -- Positive energy heals double, Negative deals double damage

9 -- Roll on Attribute Table, result increase a die size (max d12+1)

10 -- Store (not usable on self)

1 -- Agility

2 -- Smarts

5 -- Vigor

Damage Table (d10)

1 -- Negative/Unholy (Spiritual Destruction)

2 -- Heat/Fire (Increased molecular movement)

3 -- Acidic

4 -- Piercing

5 -- Slashing

6 -- Bludgeoning

7 -- Electric

8 -- Cold (Reduced molecular movement)

9 -- Positive/Holy (Spiritual Reconstruction)

10 -- Combination (roll again; Ignore future 0/10 & doubles e.g. both 3, reroll one until not 3 or 0)

Mind Exploration Levels

0 -- Manifestations -- Actions. Hears your character speak, gets punched

1 -- Projections -- Thoughts intended to reach others. Most telepathy use, shouting in head

2 -- Surface -- Thoughts for self. Voice in head (i.e. while reading)

3 -- Secrets -- Thoughts that character knows they knows, but are not voiced

4 -- Deep Secrets -- Thoughts that character does not know they know. Might stumble upon

5 -- Repression -- Thoughts that can not be accessed without quest

6+ -- Other -- Thoughts that may not be/belong in head of character (Child's depth)


Mindscapes often enable exploration of 5+ areas, albeit it hidden and often foreboding. All Eldritch Incubators suck in/trap people who go digging for level 3 (secrets) in a mindscape. So for Eldritch Incubators a simple mind read might result in discovery of Repressed information or encounters with the Child. Some even trap on level 2 (Pathfinder's Detect Thoughts).

1) Roll damage type on Damage table

2) Save type is rolled on Attribute table. Always against your Spellcasting Attribute

3) Directions are: 1=N, 2=NE, 3=E, 4=SE, 5=S, 6=SW, 7=W, 8=NW

4) Savage Worlds Inches (2 meters)

5) Ignored rolls do not count (treat as a reroll)
